Raised by a user:

{quote}
I was having trouble getting a link to a Lotus Notes document to work.
Looking through the Jira code, I found the static final List URL_PROTOCOLS in the atlassian-jira-enterprise-3.4.2-source\atlassian-renderer\src\java\com\atlassian\renderer\util\UrlUtils.java file.
I added "Notes://" to the list and the link works great now.
It seems to me that this would be better to be a system variable in a config file or something rather than a hard coded list in the java code.
Anyway, it would be nice if the Atlassian developers would at least consider adding the Notes:// url protocol to that list in the Jira code so I won't have to worry about updating that code each time I upgrade Jira.
{quote}

